However, there are rigorous age and financial criteria for the procedure (Under those rules, an abortion is free up to the 12th week of pregnancy; otherwise, patients must pay a 175 euro fee between weeks 12 and 16. If patients are between 16 and 20 years of age, the cost depends on how far along they are in their pregnancies and after three months pregnant, patients must pay 420 euros). Additionally, psychological counseling with a medical professional is required before and after the choice to have the procedure.

In 2018, 745 abortions were recorded – a jump of 14% from 2017 – with patients facing fines as well as prison sentences if they get an abortion outside of legal conditions. Contraceptive use is connected to whether or not women have an abortion. If contraception rates are higher, the abortion rate also typically increases.
